title: Demand for long-acting contraception rose sharply after 2016 election

title_detail.value: Demand for long-acting contraception rose sharply after 2016 election

summary: A new study finds that rates of long-acting, reversible contraception went up by 21.6 percent in the 30 days after the presidential election compared to rates at the same time of year in 2015.
